channel.title: Can't compile error - tut from Tonypker13
channel.description:
Hi
I've just readed the server tut from tonypker13 its a great version, really.
But one thing, i've added some options, like a "fart"-emote :D and i've translated some words to my language(dutch).
And if i want to compile it, i'll get this error: --------------------------------------------------------------- C:\Users\Pieter\Desktop\SkillScape Game\SkillScapegame100409\bulby\players\players.java:8: cannot find symbol ------------------------------------------------------------------- I've searched that line, and on that line it contains this:
import Bulby.Engine;
So, whats wrong with his?
Please Help me
Ptdb

item.title: Can't compile error - tut from Tonypker13
item.dc:creator: @Ptdragonboy Ptdragonboy
item.description:
@Ptdragonboy wrote:

[quote=“zane01, post:2, topic:272233”]Here is some advice.
Follow it in these short but simple steps.

  1. Re-download the source.
  2. Re-code it without the fart command.
  3. Dont code the codes with “dutch” only code the names of the code, or things that will be shown on the server.

For instantence, here is an example of what i mean.

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("starter")) { if (starter == 0) { addItem(995, 500000); addItem(550, 1); addItem(1856,1); addItem(565,20); addItem(892,50); addItem(4212,1); sendMessage("The starter packet for Kaseyscape Members !"); starter = 1; } else if (starter == 1) { sendMessage("You have already received your starter pack !"); } }

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("[insert dutch name here]")) { if (starter == 0) { addItem(995, 500000); addItem(550, 1); addItem(1856,1); addItem(565,20); addItem(892,50); addItem(4212,1); sendMessage("The starter packet for Kaseyscape Members !"); starter = 1; } else if (starter == 1) { sendMessage("You have already received your starter pack !"); } }[/quote]
Yes i understand, but what can be wrong with:
import Bulby.Engine; ???
